<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1399,1351,1739]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<bibRefCitation author="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C." box="[242,473,1423,1447]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="111 - 128" refId="ref43104" refString="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C. 1991. Distribution et taxonomie des Howella (Perciformes, Percichthyidae) de l'Atlantique. Cybium 15 (2): 111 - 128." type="journal article" year="1991">Post &amp; Quéro (1991)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Ogilby, 1899" authorityName="Ogilby" authorityYear="1899" box="[716,1045,1423,1447]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brodiei">
<emphasis box="[716,892,1423,1447]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Howella brodiei</emphasis>
Ogilby, 1899
</taxonomicName>
, and demonstrated the existence of two subspecies: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Post &amp; Quero, 1991)" baseAuthorityName="Post &amp; Quero" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[450,908,1455,1479]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brodiei" subSpecies="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[450,664,1455,1479]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. brodiei atlantica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C." box="[679,900,1455,1479]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="111 - 128" refId="ref43104" refString="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C. 1991. Distribution et taxonomie des Howella (Perciformes, Percichthyidae) de l'Atlantique. Cybium 15 (2): 111 - 128." type="journal article" year="1991">Post &amp; Quéro, 1991</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the North and tropical Atlantic and 
<taxonomicName authority="brodiei Ogilby, 1899" authorityName="Ogilby" authorityYear="1899" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brodiei" subSpecies="brodiei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. brodiei brodiei</emphasis>
Ogilby, 1899
</taxonomicName>
from the Indian and Pacific Oceans. The authors also showed that the number of scales between the origin of the second dorsal fin and the lateral line separates the Atlantic populations of 
<taxonomicName box="[273,363,1551,1575]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,363,1551,1575]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Howella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into two different species: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Post &amp; Quero" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[668,948,1551,1575]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brodiei" subSpecies="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[668,948,1551,1575]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Howella brodiei atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Norman, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="Norman" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1005,1395,1551,1575]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sherborni">
<emphasis box="[1005,1208,1551,1575]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Howella sherborni</emphasis>
(Norman, 1930)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Eschmeyer W. N." box="[242,441,1583,1607]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref39931" refString="Eschmeyer W. N. (ed.) 2013. The Catalog of Fishes. California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, California, U. S. A. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp and http: // collections. calacademy. org / ich /" type="url" year="2013">Eschmeyer (2013)</bibRefCitation>
raised the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="(Post &amp; Quero, 1991)" baseAuthorityName="Post &amp; Quero" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[687,1214,1583,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brodiei" subSpecies="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[687,967,1583,1607]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Howella brodiei atlantica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C." box="[983,1206,1583,1607]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="111 - 128" refId="ref43104" refString="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C. 1991. Distribution et taxonomie des Howella (Perciformes, Percichthyidae) de l'Atlantique. Cybium 15 (2): 111 - 128." type="journal article" year="1991">Post &amp; Quéro, 1991</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
to species level: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Post &amp; Quero, 1991)" baseAuthorityName="Post &amp; Quero" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[242,675,1615,1639]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[242,434,1615,1639]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Howella atlantica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C." box="[448,667,1615,1639]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="111 - 128" refId="ref43104" refString="Post A. &amp; Quero J. - C. 1991. Distribution et taxonomie des Howella (Perciformes, Percichthyidae) de l'Atlantique. Cybium 15 (2): 111 - 128." type="journal article" year="1991">Post &amp; Quéro, 1991</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ogilby" authorityYear="1899" box="[848,956,1615,1639]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brodiei">
<emphasis box="[848,956,1615,1639]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. brodiei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the northeast Atlantic should probably be considered as belonging to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Post &amp; Quero" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[566,693,1647,1671]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Howellidae" genus="Howella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[566,693,1647,1671]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
